{"type":"message","id":"63306710","parentId":"081e96fb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:25:28.170Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_aynmtkv7xggq_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 2736\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=745\r\n[mutation proposed] research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[master 5912a95] pulse: 2026-03-24 152514\n 6 files changed, 124 insertions(+), 94 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 152514.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 152514.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 152414.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 152514 - The CFI compression experiment revealed that pure threshold filtering is too aggressive (loses 92.9% recall), but identified that constant-format tokens (freq�160, CFI=1) are the contamination source. The next logical step is to implement and test Strategy C: the hybrid scoring formula that should distinguish metaprogramming artifacts from true research signals.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"nova-daisy","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 2736\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=745\r\n[mutation proposed] research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[master 5912a95] pulse: 2026-03-24 152514\n 6 files changed, 124 insertions(+), 94 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 152514.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 152514.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 152414.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 152514 - The CFI compression experiment revealed that pure threshold filtering is too aggressive (loses 92.9% recall), but identified that constant-format tokens (freq�160, CFI=1) are the contamination source. The next logical step is to implement and test Strategy C: the hybrid scoring formula that should distinguish metaprogramming artifacts from true research signals.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380328168}}
{"type":"message","id":"a6ecc642","parentId":"63306710","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:25:28.173Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_aynmtkv7xggq_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 152414\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most effective action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- Recent CFI compression experiment completed with key findings\r\n- Next experiment identified: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring (Strategy C)\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Need to test if this distinguishes \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action is to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. This is the identified pending task that would advance the compression research.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what files I need to create/modify:\r\n1. I need to set up the experiment script that implements the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Run the experiment on 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n3. Compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nBut first, I should check if there's existing code I can build on. The CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md mentions a previous experiment setup. Let me look for the existing experiment code.\r\n\r\nActually, I should implement the hybrid scoring experiment. Let me check what exists in the codebase.\r\n\r\nSince I'm stateless and need to take one concrete action, I should:\r\n1. Create or modify the experiment script to implement Strategy C (Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring)\r\n2. This will be the concrete next step toward the pending experiment\r\n\r\nLet me check if there's an existing experiment file in research/ or scripts/\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment identified that binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60) fail because \"constant format\" tokens like \"pulse\" (freq=160, CFI=1) look causal but aren't. The next step is to implement and test the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment script that implements Strategy C, using the existing pulse dataset from the previous experiment to compare hybrid scoring against binary thresholds on 200 pulses with 80/20 split.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# Comparing against binary threshold approach\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# === CONFIG ===\r\n$PULSES_DIR = \"state/pulses\"\r\n$SPLIT = @{ train = 0.8; test = 0.2 }\r\n$OUTPUT = \"research/hybrid_scoring_results.md\"\r\n$NUM_PULSES = 200\r\n\r\n# === SCORING FUNCTIONS ===\r\n\r\n# Strategy A: Binary CFI threshold (from previous experiment)\r\nfunction Get-BinaryScore {\r\n    param($token, $cfiThreshold = 0.7, $freqMax = 120)\r\n    if ($token.cfi -ge $cfiThreshold -and $token.freq -ge 3 -and $token.freq -lt $freqMax) {\r\n        return 1.0\r\n    }\r\n    return 0.0\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring (NEW)\r\n# Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Expected: constant \"pulse\" (freq=160, CFI=1) gets score = 1 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0\r\n#           research token (freq=80, CFI=0.7) gets score = 0.7 × 0.667 = 0.467\r\n# BUT this still doesn't discriminate! Need freq ceiling.\r\nfunction Get-HybridScore {\r\n    param($token, $freqTarget = 120)\r\n    $freqNorm = [Math]::Min(1.0, $token.freq / $freqTarget)\r\n    return $token.cfi * $freqNorm\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Strategy D: Hybrid with freq ceiling (penalize constant tokens)\r\n# score(T) = CFI(T) × freq(T)/freqTarget if freq < freqTarget, else 0\r\n# This zeroes out tokens above threshold - the key discriminator!\r\nfunction Get-HybridWithCeiling {\r\n    param($token, $freqTarget = 120)\r\n    if ($token.freq -ge $freqTarget) {\r\n        return 0.0  # Penalize constant-format tokens\r\n    }\r\n    $freqNorm = $token.freq / $freqTarget\r\n    return $token.cfi * $freqNorm\r\n}\r\n\r\n# === LOAD PULSES ===\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem $PULSES_DIR -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name | Select-Object -First $NUM_PULSES\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($pulseFiles.Count) pulses\"\r\n\r\n# Build token corpus with CFI and frequency\r\n$tokenData = @{}\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    foreach ($t in $tokens) {\r\n        if (-not $tokenData.ContainsKey($t)) {\r\n            $tokenData[$t] = @{ freq = 0; cfi = 0; docs = 0 }\r\n        }\r\n        $tokenData[$t].freq++\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI for each token (probability token appears in doc)\r\n$totalDocs = $pulseFiles.Count\r\nforeach ($t in $tokenData.Keys) {\r\n    $tokenData[$t].cfi = $tokenData[$t].freq / $totalDocs\r\n}\r\n\r\n# === EVALUATE STRATEGIES ===\r\n$tokens = $tokenData\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:24:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380328170}}
